posts.text:
Communiqué de Mme Emmanuelle Ménard, dans le cadre de la Loi de finances rectificative 2017 

L’invalidation par le Conseil constitutionnel, le 6 octobre dernier, de la taxe de 3% sur les dividendes, votée en 2012 sous la précédente majorité socialiste, va obliger l’Etat à rembourser environ 10 milliards d’euros aux grandes entreprises. L’Assemblée nationale se penchait aujourd’hui, en urgence, sur les solutions proposées par le Gouvernement pour opérer ce remboursement... 

« Un scandale d’Etat » selon Bruno Lemaire, ministre de l’Economie... « Un amateurisme juridique » selon Christophe Castaner, le porte-parole du Gouvernement... 
Et j’ajouterai : « Une belle leçon d’hypocrisie » puisque tout ce petit monde fait semblant de ne pas connaître les responsabilités dans cette affaire... 

Cette taxe a été mise en place par Monsieur Moscovici, alors ministre de l’Economie du gouvernement Ayrault. 
Et qui était alors le directeur de cabinet de monsieur Moscovici ? Alexis Kohler, l’actuel secrétaire général de l’Elysée ! 
Autre question : qui était alors la directrice de cabinet de Jérôme Cahuzac, ministre du Budget ? Nulle autre qu’Amélie Verdier, l’actuelle directrice du Budget, chargée aujourd’hui de trouver… les fameux 10 milliards à rembourser. 
Mais ne nous arrêtons pas en si bon chemin. Qui était alors le secrétaire général adjoint de l’Elysée en charge des questions économiques et fiscales, personne d’autre qu’Emmanuel Macron ! 
Alors, faire semblant aujourd’hui de tomber des nues, c’est tout simplement se moquer du monde ! 

Last but not least, le rapporteur général ose affirmer dans l’hémicycle : « l’Etat prend à sa charge la moitié du remboursement. » L’Etat ? Non, les contribuables français, une fois de plus... 

Alors, aujourd’hui, chacun doit prendre ses responsabilités. Les socialistes au pouvoir hier encore. Mais aussi Emmanuel Macron qui ne peut se défausser de son rôle dans cet immense raté... 

Une question de devoir, ou d’honneur... Emmanuelle Ménard, Député de l'Hérault (07-11-17) 519 vues

posts.text:
Taiwan Open of Surfing 2017 to Kick Off in Taitung November 07, 2017 03:32 ET | Source: Taitung County Government photo-release Surfing enthusiasts from all over the world will gather in Taitung Taitung County Government 
Taitung, Taiwan,   This year, Taitung County Government received an invitation from the World Surf League to host the Men’s and Women’s Longboard Championships in Taiwan for the first time. The tournament will take place in Jinzun, Donghe Township, and is one of the WSL’s four worldwide championships being held. In addition, Taitung will continue to hold the WSL Men’s Qualifying Series 1500, making it the 56th destination so far. 
Besides the longboard championships, the WSL’s Men’s Longboard Asia and Oceania Region tournaments will be part of the happenings in Jinzun from November 23 rd until December 3 rd . 
With the arrival of the fall season comes the northeast monsoon winds, which brings about magnificent waves at Jinzun. Not only are they a hit with local surfers, but they have also caught the eye of international elite surfing enthusiasts. It is expected that local surfing fans and competitors all descend upon Jinzun in Taitung to witness the championships, see their idols up close, and to observe the skills of those elite surfers, while at the same giving visitors from across the world the opportunity to get to know Taiwan, and in particular, Taitung. 
Local surfing enthusiasts were able to register to participate on the event’s official Facebook page until October 13 th . This year’s schedule includes the Women’s Pro, Master, Pro Junior, Club Team, and much more! We encourage all local and foreign friends alike to join us in Jinzun, Taitung for this year’s championships. Let’s give all competitors our support and encouragement! 
Please visit the official Facebook page below for any upcoming news and updates. 
Dates: November 23 until December 3Location: JInzun Harbor, Donghe Township, Taitung County

posts.title: U.S. Lawns Volunteers for Second Harvest Food Bank of Central Florida
posts.text:
U.S. Lawns Home Office team and local franchisees volunteered time to help provide meals to families in need.

(PRWEB) November 07, 2017

U.S. Lawns, a commercial grounds care company with a nationwide franchise network in over 250 locations, is proud of their Home Office Team and local franchisees for volunteering time to help Second Harvest Food Bank of Central Florida. In just one Saturday afternoon, U.S. Lawns, along with other volunteers, were able to organize and box up 8,138 pounds of food for a total of 6,782 meals.

Second Harvest Food Bank works with 550 local feeding partners and last year provided 54 million meals to families, kids and seniors. Through their distribution network, this food is often in the hands of people in need later the same day it arrives in their warehouse. They are also a member of Feeding America, a nationwide network of more than 200 food banks that helps feed people across the country after natural disasters, like hurricanes, floods, fires, tornadoes, etc.

Second Harvest also transforms dozens of lives directly every year. Economically-challenged adults graduate from their 14-week culinary training program and are placed in ‘better than minimum wage’ jobs that set them and their families on a path to self-sustainability.

"Our brand position as a franchisor is to Improve Your Community. Improve Your Life," said U.S. Lawns President Ken Hutcheson. "There’s no greater cause than providing food for families, seniors and others who may otherwise not receive what they need. That’s why we chose to help out Second Harvest. And Second Harvest’s culinary training provides hope and courage to people to help them transform their future."

U.S. Lawns is committed to doing their part to give back to communities nationwide, and honored to support Second Harvest Food Bank because they reflect the essence of the U.S. Lawns vision.

About U.S. Lawns Founded in 1986, U.S. Lawns services commercial customers through a nationwide franchise network in over 250 locations, providing professional grade, customized grounds care and snow & ice management services to corporate campuses, retail centers, industrial parks, multi-family residential communities and other commercial customers. posts.title: PIP skontrolowała sklepy Biedronka. Problem z ewidencją czasu pracy
posts.text:
• Inspektorzy ujawnili m.in. nierzetelne prowadzenie ewidencji czasu pracy. 
• Nie jest wykluczone, że kontrole odbędą się także na szerszą skalę. 
• Biedronka jest drugim największym pracodawcą w Polsce, zatrudnia 55 tys. osób. 
PIP przesłuchała ponad 100 osób. Jak pisze „Dziennik Gazeta Prawna”, inspektorzy ujawnili nierzetelne prowadzenie ewidencji czasu pracy oraz nieprzestrzeganie przepisów o urlopach wypoczynkowych. 
Inne nieprawidłowości dotyczyły planowania czasu pracy, np. planowania dni wolnych w okresie zwolnienia lekarskiego czy zlecanie pracy osobom wychowującym dziecko do lat czterech w godzinach nadliczbowych. 
W sklepie w Poznaniu praca w godzinach nadliczbowych była wykazywana w tzw. pamiętniku sklepu zamiast w karcie ewidencji. Pracownikom nie wypłacano dodatków za pracę w godzinach nadliczbowych, odmawiano im też prawa do skorzystania z 15-minutowej przerwy. 
W niektórych sklepach naruszono też zasady bezpieczeństwa. Wyjścia ewakuacyjne były zastawione towarem, a pracownicy obsługiwali wózki elektryczne bez stosownego przeszkolenia. 
Jeronimo Martins nie otrzymało jeszcze wyników kontroli od PIP. Nie jest wykluczone, że PIP dokona w przyszłości kontroli sklepów Biedronka na szerszą skalę. 
Kontrole na wniosek związkowców 
Kontrole w sklepach Biedronka to pokłosie wydarzeń z czerwca tego roku, gdy członkowie NSZZ „Solidarność” złożyli skargę do inspekcji pracy. Zarzucano m.in., że pracodawca nie zapewnia jednej na cztery tygodnie wolnej niedzieli. Ostatecznie tego akurat zarzutu inspektorom PIP nie udało się potwierdzić . 
O przeprowadzenie kontroli przestrzegania przepisów prawa pracy w sieci oraz siedzibie Jeronimo Martins Polska wnioskował również Stanisław Szwed, sekretarz stanu w Ministerstwie Rodziny, Pracy i Polityki Społecznej. 
Jeronimo Martins, właściciel sieci Biedronka, jest drugim, po Poczcie Polskiej, największym pracodawcą w Polsce. Biedronka zatrudnia w naszym kraju ponad 55 tys. osób.

问：我需要数作文的字数吗？
答：在平时练习的时候尽量要做到写完以后数字数。其实只要做到论点论据相结合，字数是一定不会少的。但是很多同学都会碰到练习写作到后面就觉得无法停下来。因此一定要数字数来进行控制。比较好的一个方法就是用附在书后的考试答题纸的样板来写作文。平时写作的字体大小就是考试时的字体大小，心里面有个大致的概念自己一行里大约会写多少字，从而在真实考试场景下就可以用很少的时间来检测自己在字数方面的任务了。
问：如果写不到规定的字数怎么办？
答：写不到字数是肯定会扣分的。规定字数是150个，如果只写到139个，则一定会被扣1分。但是如果能写到145个字，则考官会认为“文章长度可以接受”，可能根据文章的水平来评判，不至于扣掉1分。同样的规则适用于250个字的大作文。
问：如果我字数写的太多了怎么办？
答：如果字数太多的话，那就应该检查一下是不是有一些冗长的、不必要的描述，不要因为这些不必要的信息而导致被扣分，那就得不偿失了。另外，如果一篇写的太长，肯定要影响到另一篇作文的发挥，因为一共只有1个小时的时间。尤其是如果因为小作文而忽视了大作文，在总分上受影响的程度就更大了。 Ýp!UDwy3bbs.chuguo.cn¨nËMä/ÎÔ

Duties include: Monitoring direct care services to individuals with intellectual disabilities; Assure correct implementation of ADL/ILS, dinning, CTP and use of equipment by direct observation and participation in the ISP programs, assist in the implementation of clinical programs; maintain confidential records of individuals; attend individual’s review meetings; accompany individuals to various appointments; provide leisure activities to individuals; assist individuals in meeting his/her personal care and nutritional needs; assist and support individual in making choices in his/her life; maintain individual’s rights by complying with applicable laws and regulations; may drive individuals to work, appointments, and recreational outings; and perform related work as required. 
• Provides ongoing daily supervision and training to DSW I’s and II’s in order to provide optimal support to Individuals to promote personal well being and personal growth. Meets with direct care staff to discuss supervisory issues. Provides feed back to management regarding discipline as appropriate. Participates with Divisional Management in progressive discipline process. 
• Assures active treatment as part of the team process through the development and coordination of supports to ensure personal growth; community participation and the development of relationships. Assesses, develops, monitors, modifies and documents all ADL/ILS programs. Develops and maintains Daily activity schedules with consideration for the potential of violent behaviors, provides ongoing training to staff to assure proper implementation of the ISP. Participates in ISP, team and transitional meetings. Implements and monitors timeout procedures; Implements and monitors restraints; Implements and monitors Mechanical Restraints; Trains staff on behavioral interventions and procedures such as use of Mechanical Restraints and/or CTP; Coordinates use of staff on the crisis unit.

posts.text:
Rivalry put aside for news that new Intel chips will come with AMD Radeon graphics. Shares 
One of the technology industry's biggest rivalries may well be over after AMD and Intel announced they are teaming up in building new chips . 
Yes, you read that right. AMD and Intel will be co-designing an Intel Core microprocesor, and the crazy part is – it's about bringing high-level graphics processing to ultra-thin laptops. According to a joint press release, the new chip will be an “evolution” of Intel 8th gen chis and H-series Core chips. 
Besides speeds and state-of-the-art graphics, the new chip will also consume less energy, making it even more suitable for laptops. The chip is expected to start shipping in the first quarter of 2018, which is also quite the surprise. 
According to media reports , rumours of this chip have been circulating around for some time now, with people referring to it as Kaby Lake G. However Intel calls all of that “rumour and speculation”. 
This breakthrough is made possible thanks to EMIB, or Embedded Multi-die interconnect Bridge. 
Intel explains: “At the heart of this new design is EMIB, a small intelligent bridge that allows heterogeneous silicon to quickly pass information in extremely close proximity. EMIB eliminates height impact as well as manufacturing and design complexities, enabling faster, more powerful and more efficient products in smaller sizes. This is the first consumer product that takes advantage of EMIB.” 
“Our collaboration with Intel expands the installed base for AMD Radeon GPUs and brings to market a differentiated solution for high-performance graphics,” said Scott Herkelman, vice president and general manager, AMD Radeon Technologies Group. “Together we are offering gamers and content creators the opportunity to have a thinner-and-lighter PC capable of delivering discrete performance-tier graphics experiences in AAA games and content creation applications. This new semi-custom GPU puts the performance and capabilities of Radeon graphics into the hands of an expanded set of enthusiasts who want the best visual experience possible.”
